{"questionId":"9066391","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Dinitrogen monoxide, N<sub>2</sub>O, causes depletion of ozone in the stratosphere.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The Lewis (electron dot) structure of the dinitrogen monoxide molecule can be represented as:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/5985/3d.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"373\" height=\"54\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Deduce the hybridization of the central nitrogen atom in the molecule.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">sp &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066391","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ2.d(iii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the hybridization of the central nitrogen atom in the molecule.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d(iii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure","14.2 Hybridization","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}